let bzTip39 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: _______", body: "Scientific studies suggest that 25% of how how long we live is dictated by genes. The other 75% is determined by our lifestyles and the everyday choices we make.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")



let bzTip41 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: _______", body: "They receive immediate care when injured or ill, and perhaps most significantly, felt loved and a sense of belonging. A happy by-product was that grandparents stayed involved in children's lives. Grandparents provide love, childcare, financial help, wisdom, expectations, and motivation to perpetuate traditions and push children to succeed. This may add up to healthier, better adjussted, and longer-lived children, and it seems to certainly give the population a healthy bump in longevity.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")// p.52


//Now/Home
let bzTip43 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Talk a walk", body: "Walking provides the type of low-intensity exercise that yeilds all the cardiovascular benefits you might expect, but it also has a positive effect on muscles and bones - without the joint-pounding damage caused by running marathons or triathlons.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//Unsure about this claim?


//Tonight/Home/Weekend/Stressed
let bzTip44 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Laugh with friends and family", body: "Laughter reduces stress, which can lower one's risk of cardiovascular disease.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

//Meal/Groceries


//Tonight
let bzTip46 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Listen to a family member in need tonight", body: "People who live in strong, healthy familes suffer lower rates of depression, suicide, and stress. Supporting your family members will help you and your family live happier and healthier lives.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip47 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Avoid eating meat at every meal", body: "Too much meat can increase your chances of obesity; a study of people who lived to 100+ years old in Okinawa, Japan, found that they ate meat only during holidays and festivals.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip48 = Tip(header: "", title: "Life advice from a 102 year-old woman on the secret to living to 102", body: "\"I used to be very beautiful. It took me a long time to realize that beauty is within. It comes from not worrying so much about your own problems. Sometimes you can best take care of yourself by taking care of others... Eat your vegetables, have a positive outlook, be kind to people, and smile.\"", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

//60+
let bzTip49 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Have a reason for waking up in the morning", body: "A sudden loss of a person's traditional role can have a measurable effect on mortality. We see this especially among teachers and police officers who die very soon after they quit working. Police and teachers have very clear senses of purpose and relatively high status. Once they retire, they lose both of those qualities and they tend to decline rapidly.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip50 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Buy soy products (soy milk, tofu, and edamame)", body: "Soy has the ability to lower the level of \"bad\" cholesterol in the body and the potential to reduce the risk of heart disease. Protein content may vary among forms and producers, so be sure to check the labels. \n\nBuy fermented soy products over nonfermented soy products whenever possible because fermented soy has more nutritional value.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip51 = Tip(header: "", title: "Making more friends reduces stress", body: "On average, an American has only 2 close friends he or she can count on, recently down from 3, which may contribute to an increasing sense of stress. Chronic stress takes a toll on overall health.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip52 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Don't eat junk food because it creates chronic inflammation of the gastrointestinal track", body: "Excessive or unnecessary inflammation from eating bad foods causes the body to produce chemicals that wreak havoc on our organs and arteries. Over time, this accelerates heart disease, bone loss, Alzheimer's disease.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip53 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: ________", body: "Antioxidants found in vegetables and herbs are important, because the same oxidation process that rusts our cars also deteriorates our bodies. Antioxidants clean up highly charged oxygen-free radicals that cause this sort of rust.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//p.95??

//Morning
let bzTip54 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Get 10-15 minutes of sun exposure twice weekly, then apply SPF 15+ sunscreen afterward", body: "That should provide enough sun to produce vitamin D without exposing the skin too many damaging UV rays. Vitamin D promotes stronger bones and healthier bodies.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip55 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Get 10-15 minutes of sun exposure twice weekly, then apply SPF 15+ sunscreen afterward", body: "That should provide enough sun to produce vitamin D without exposing the skin too many damaging UV rays. Being who stay inside all the time would have to drink gallons of fortified milk every day to optimize their vitamin D. The amount of vitamin D in a multivitamin is not enough.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")


//Meal
let bzTip56 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Eat a plant-based diet and only eat meat on special occasions", body: "A study of 100+ year-old living in Okinawa, Japan, found that they ate a plant-based diet most of their lives. Their meals or stir-fried vegetables, sweet potatoes, and tofu are high in nutrients and low in calories. While they do eat some pork, it is traditionally reserved only for infrequent ceremonial occasions and taken only in small amounts.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

//Home
let bzTip57 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Make a garden", body: "A study of 100+ year-olds in Okinawa, Japan, found that almost all grow or once grew a garden. It's a source of daily physical activity that exercises the body with a wide range of motion and helps reduce stress. It's also a near-constant source of fresh vegetables.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

//Restaurant?
let bzTip58 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Eat more soy products (soy milk, tofu, and edamame)", body: "A study of 100+ year-olds living in Okinawa, Japan, found that their diet is rich foods made with soy, like tofu and miso soup. Flavonoids in tofu may help protect the heart and guard against breast cancer. \n\nFermented soy products contribute to a healthy intestinal ecology and offer even better nutritional benefits than nonfermented soy products.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip59 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Eating fruits, vegetables, and whole grains seems to protect against a wide variety of cancers", body: "Study: nonvegetarians had about twice the risk of heart disease as vegetarians.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip60 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Drink 8+ cups of water a day", body: "About 60% of you body's total weight is water. According to the Mayo Clinic, it takes an average of 8 cups of water (along with a healthy diet) to replace what your body uses normally every day. \n\nModerate exercise increases the amount by 1-2 cups. Strenuous exercise (lasting 1+ hours) ups the average intake by 2 to 3 cups per hour exercised.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip61 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Never pass a water fountain without having a drink", body: "According to the Mayo Clinic, it takes an average of 8 cups of water (along with a healthy diet) to replace what your body uses normally every day. \n\nModerate exercise increases the amount by 1-2 cups. Strenuous exercise (lasting 1+ hours) ups the average intake by 2 to 3 cups per hour exercised.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip62 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Laughing more. It reduces your risk of a heart attack", body: "A study found that laughter helped relax blood vessels, linking it to healthier function and a possible decreased risk of heart attack. Others have found that laughter may lower blood pressure and increase the amount of disease-fighting cells found in the body.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip63 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Get regular, moderate exercise. You don't need to be a marathoner to maximize your life expectancy", body: "Getting regular, low-intensity exercise like daily walks appears to help reduce your chances of having heart disease and certain cancers.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip64 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Snack on nuts", body: "Study: People who consume nuts at least 5 times a week have half the risk of heart disease and live about 2 years longer than those who don't. At least 4 major studies have confirmed that eating nuts has an impact on health and life expectancy.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip65 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Eat meat in moderation", body: "Study: Consuming fruits, vegetables, and whole grains seems to be protective against a wide variety of cancers. For those who prefer to eat some meat, try small portions served as a side dish rather than as the main meal.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip66 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Eat an early, light dinner", body: "\"Eat breakfast like a king, lunch like a prince, and dinner like a pauper,\" American nutritionist Adell Davis is said to have recommended. A light dinner early in the evening avoids flooding the body with calories during the inactive parts of the day. It seems to promote better sleep and a lower BMI.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip67 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Eating fruits, vegetables, and whole grains seems to be protective for a wide variety of cancers", body: "Study: Women who ate tomatoes at least 3-4 times a week reduced their chance of getting ovarian cancer by 70% over those who ate tomatoes less often. Men who ate a lot of tomatoes also reduced their chance of getting prostate cancer. \n\nStudy: Nonsmokers who ate 2+ servings of fruit per day had about 70% fewer lung cancers than nonsmokers who ate fruit only once or twice a week. \n\nStudy: People who ate legumes such as peas and beans 3 times a week had a 30%-40% reduction in colon cancer.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")





//40+
let bzTip70 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: People 40+ need more calcium to reduce bone loss", body: "Our bones are constantly losing mass and building it back up. However, after 40, we lose bone faster than we build it. Calcium may help slow that loss. \n\nLastly, that loss of bone strength can also make older people more susceptible to hip fractures, which is one of the leading causes of death for older people. \n\nCalcium is found in kale, broccoli, sardines, yogurt, milk, and cheese.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP p.203

let bzTip71 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Having faith in a higher power reduces stress in your life", body: "Study: Participants who attended religious services about once a month or more had up to a 35% reduced risk of death for the next 7 years. \n\nAnother study that focused on 100+ year-olds found that many of them believe in a higher power. Believing that a higher power is in control of their lives relieves any economic, spiritual, or well-being anxiety that might otherwise have. They go through life with the peaceful certitude that someone is looking out for them.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP p.209



let bzTip73 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Live with your family", body: "A study of 100+ year-olds in Costa Rica found they tend to live with their families, and children or grandchildren provide support and sense of purpose and belonging. This provides a physical and psychological safety net.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")

let bzTip74 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Eat a light dinner early in the evening", body: "Eating fewer calories appears to be one of the best ways to add years to your life.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//Kinda weak



// Morning/Day


//Grocery




//Kitchen


let bzTip80 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Drink herbal teas everyday because they make you pee. Not peeing enough causes toxic compounds to build, which may increase blood pressure", body: "High blood pressure increases your risk of dementia, heart attacks, and strokes. \n\nRotate flavors (sage, chamomile, peppermint, hibiscus, oregano, and rosemary) to not get too much of any one compound.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP

let bzTip81 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Occasional napping decreased a person's risk of heart disease by 12% and regular napping decreased a person's risk of heart disease by 37%", body: "It may be because napping lowers stress hormones or rests the heart. Or it may be because nappers tend to live healthier lives.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP

let bzTip82 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Fast occasionally", body: "Caloric restriction - a type of fasting that cuts about 30% of calories out of the normal diet - is the only proven way to slow the aging process in mammals. Regularly and moderately reducing calories, either as part of a diet or as part of a religious practice, may yield some longevity benefits.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP

let bzTip83 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Make family and friends a top priority", body: "Social connections have been shown to increase overall health and longevity. Researchers who analyzed 148 different studies found that people who weren't connected to their communities had a 50% greater chance of dying during the follow-up period of 7.5 years (on average) than those who had strong social networks.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP

//Grocery store





let bzTip86 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Adding just 2 ounces of beans to your daily diet is associated with a longer life", body: "", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP

let bzTip87 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Having a life's purpose adds years to your life", body: "Study: You're more likely to die the year you retire than you are during your last year of work.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP



//Grocery



//WIP
let bzTip20 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Having a glass of wine with your meal helps you makes it more likely you'll eat slower", body: "", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP
let bzTip22 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Answer this question: Why do you get up in the morning?", body: "Study: Individuals who expressed a clear goal in life - something to get up for in the morning, something that made a difference - lived longer and were sharper than those who did not. \n\nConsider what you're passionate about, how you enjoy using your talents, and what is truly important to you.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP p.283

let bzTip23 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Slow down your life's pace to reduce your risk of age-related diseases", body: "Stress causes inflammation in the body. Over time, the negative effects of inflammation may increase your risk of age-related diseases such as Alzheimer's disease, diabetes, and cardiovascular disease. A 107 year-old's advice for younger people is \"Life is short. Don't run so fast you miss it.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP p.285

let bzTip88 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Drink wine while eating plants", body: "The body absorbs more of the flavonoids, the artery-scrubbing antioxidants.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP

//Home
let bzTip24 = Tip(header: "", title: "Live longer: Rid your home of as many TVs and electronic devices as possible, or limit them to just one room", body: "Most electronic entertainment clutters your mind, which can cause stress. Stress causes inflammation in your body. Overtime, inflammation caused by stress increases your risk of Alzheimer's disease, diabetes, and cardiovascular disease. \n\nMinimize time spent on electronic devices to keep chronic inflammation in check.", sourceName: "The Blue Zones: 9 Lessons For Living Longer", sourceURL: "https://www.amazon.com/Blue-Zones-Lessons-Living-Longest/dp/1426207557", sponsorLogo: "", sponsorURL: "")//WIP p.285
